HELP CASE                                               A. Sloman, March 1982

    switchon <start-condition>
        <one or more CASE or NOTCASE clauses>
        <optional ELSE clause>
    endswitchon

The word CASE is used with the SWITCHON facility, which permits abbreviation
of multi-branch conditional statements where part of the condition is the same
for all branches.

See HELP
    *SWITCHON - for detailed description of SWITCHON facility
    *ANDCASE  - syntax word also used with SWITCHON
